
This directory contains examples of Aether input files.

aether_cubesphere.json - runs 10 minutes of cubesphere grid, outputs corners.
  - 6 processors needed.

aether_sphere.json - runs 10 minutes of spherical grid, outputs corners.
  - 4 processors recommended.

To run part of the March 17, 2013 storm:
  - go into the srcPython directory
  - run test_electrodynamics.sh, which produces binary electrodynamics files and
    png files that show the potential and aurora.
    copy the b20130317n_omni_ions.bin and omni_20130317.txt files to the run directory.
  - go into the run directory and copy the aether_20130317.json to aether.json.
